{
  "texts": [
    "Beyond equity of access, there are other ethical concerns.",
    "While this paper focuses on the practical use of AI as a way to expand and transform the classroom, there are also wider implications to using AI that educators may want to consider before deciding whether to use these systems.",
    "Large Language Models are trained in ways that may violate copyright, and often rely on the efforts of low-wage workers in precarious conditions for part of their training.",
    "Models are trained on biased data and can produce either subtly or overtly biased results.",
    "And because these biases seem to come from an objective machine, they can be especially pernicious (Bender et. al, 2021)."
  ]
}